denfrm31.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1867.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"></a>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm31.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1867.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"></a>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm31.emailToFriend?topicID=1867.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/email.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="email this topic to a friend"></a> </td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#200985><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/ubbarden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bbarden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bbarden.com/userfiles/bb-icon.jpg" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/userfiles/y-fireball-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>it's coming in v1.8<br />Webmaster<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-4-6.gif' /></span><br>  ezSupporter<br> Posts: <b>6896</b><br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#99CCFF>Posted: 9/2/02 4:31:05 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> <img src="http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/ponder.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: One sig per topic rule</span><hr size=1> I can understand what you're saying, Sudsy.  Based on your reply and some of the rest, here is where I stand on this.<br>
<br>
I do like a lot of the graphics that people use in their sigs, and I like to see them.  However, some are not exactly small, and it creates a heck of a lot more scrolling in a long topic if the sigs are left on the whole way through.  And to be honest, it makes the board look messy.<br>
<br>
It gets even worse when the replies are barely longer than a few words.  On some boards I've seen topics that have a lot of very short posts with huge sigs.  As a result it becomes hard to see any of the discussion - and after all, this is a discussion board.  Free For All is not a graphics gallery - imagery can be shown off in the Creativity Corner.<br>
<br>
Maybe it would be more appropriate if we enabled sigs in the Creativity Corner, Arrivals forum and Power Designs... and scrap sigs elsewhere.  When you arrive here, you can show us your sig.  When you want to show off a new image that you're using in your sig, you can post in the Creativity Corner.  When you want us to visit your site (for comment, obviously - not just for the sake of advertising), Power Designs is where it's at.<br>
<br>
Remember that every post you make contains a link to your profile.  You don't need to put a sig in every post you make.<br>
<br>
Say you start a topic in the Power Designs forum, asking for comments on your web site.  The link is in your sig.  OK, so we check it out and reply.  Then the next reply contains the same sig that we saw in the first post.  Why do we need to see it again?<br>
<br>
I'm beginning to think that permitting sigs should only be in the forums where those sigs serve a purpose.  If you're simply chatting, you don't need a sig in any of your posts to be honest.<br>
<br>
Mind you I'm a fine one to talk.  Sample IM convo: &quot;Hi Ben, how are you?&quot; ... &quot;I'm ok, seen my web site lately?&quot; Yeah I know I'm bad...<br>
<br>
So what does everybody think? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :ponder --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/ponder.gif ALT=":ponder"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
